        <h1>HERO ROLES</h1>
        <p>
            The Heroes of Overwatch and Talon possess a dizzying variety of weapons and abilities.
            Nevertheless, they operate on the same battlefields and pursue the same goals. Every
            shot you take, projectile you block, or wound you heal, must be coordinated on the
            Objective. By using your Hero's unique skills to fulfill your Role in the Team, you will
            ensure that your skill and hard work do not go to waste.
        </p>
        <div class="Hint_Winston">
            <img src="img/hint_winston.png" />
            <div>
                Getting good with a Hero means learning them in more than just one Role. You have to
                learn <b>every</b> Role!
                <div></div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <p>
            The six Roles are designed to build a team that can react effectively to any situation.
            That doesn't mean <i>every</i> match and <i>every</i> situation calls for all six Roles
            to be filled. In fact, it becomes impossible as soon as the first kill is made! It's
            crucial that Agents understand that a Role is an assignment for the ideal circumstance.
            Planning for the best possible outcome gives that outcome the best possible chance of
            occurring. As soon as the best case scenario has been ruled out, each Agent must adapt
            on the fly, filling the Role which the team most needs moment to moment.
        </p>
            Experienced Agents may note that this arrangement superficially resembles the classic
            <a href="strategy/comps#two_two_two">2-2-2 Team Composition</a>. Don't be fooled - many
            Roles can be filled by a diverse cast of Heroes. By approaching the Hero Select Screen
            with an open mind toward which Heroes can fulfill which Roles, a wide variety of
            functioning <a href="strategy/comps">Team Compositions</a> can be designed.
        </p>
        <h3>RESEARCH AND FIELD EXPERIENCE</h3>
        <p>
            Be advised that the Roles indicated as appropriate for each Hero are suggestions. They are
            based on the best information that the Academy has acquired and until you have become an
            experienced Agent you are advised to follow them. However, as you gather new intel in the
            field you are <i>encouraged</i> to develop your own theories, no matter how much they
            may contradict Academy doctrine. This is your war, Agent. Fight it how you choose.
        </p>
