                <p class="RoleSummary">Main DPS</p>
                <p>
                    Sometimes nothing but unrelenting sustained fire will get the job done. By
                    providing continuous steady pressure, the Assaulter taxes the Enemy's defenses
                    and punishes them whenever those defenses fail.
                </p>
                <p>
                    The Assaulter's primary objective is to apply continuous pressure against the
                    enemy Point, forcing out defensive abilities and preventing the Enemy from
                    leaving cover. The Assaulter should leverage the defensive capabilities of their
                    own <a href="strategy/roles#point">Point</a> to keep the enemy occupied and
                    stressed as long as possible. The Assaulter's secondary objective is usually the
                    enemy Assaulter. Once the enemy Team's ability to apply damage to the Objective
                    has been crippled, the Assaulter is free to make kills of opportunity against
                    the nearest Enemy targets to <a href="strategy/tactics#rout">"clean up"</a> the
                    fight.
                </p>
                <p>
                    In a <a href="strategy/comp#dive">Dive Comp</a>, the Assaulter usually
                    targets the enemy Support Heroes first. They should then focus on the enemy
                    Point and Assaulter as normal.
                </p>
                <p>
                    As long as the enemy Team is applying damage to the Objective, the Assaulter's
                    job is not done. When the enemy team's Assaulter is a long range class, they
                    must be killed or forced out of position before the Objective can be considered
                    fully secure. In some situations, the
                    <a href="strategy/roles#skirmisher">Skirmisher</a> will be available to engage
                    the enemy Assaulter. When this is the case, the Assaulter should position
                    further forward to support them.
                </p>
                <p>
                    A good Assaulter Hero is always capable of strong sustained DPS. Self-healing
                    abilities and offensive abilities that disable individual enemies are very
                    valuable in an Assaulter. Mobility is less valuable as the Assaulter usually
                    positions close to their <a href="strategy/roles#captain">Captain</a>.
                </p>
            </div>
